We were building paths in PathWeaver and saving the generated json output files to our VSCode project folder src/main/deploy/output. The path files are in PathWeaver/Paths in our top level project directory. This has always been working successfully, then all of a sudden it just stopped generating the json output files. We restarted everything including the PC thinking that it was java jar file problem, but no luck. We pushed the project to github and tried it on another PC. That didn’t work either. Our PathWeaver project is pointed to the correct directories and loads all of the path files. Here’s our pathweaver.json file:

{
  "lengthUnit": "Meter",
  "exportUnit": "Always Meters",
  "maxVelocity": 1.0,
  "maxAcceleration": 1.0,
  "trackWidth": 0.7,
  "gameName": "Charged Up",
  "outputDir": "../src/main/deploy"
}

Has this happened to anyone else? We’ve tried everything we can think of to get this working. Thank you.
